you gotta go through the bank.

26:33.010 --> 26:34.178
No, I'm--

26:34.678 --> 26:35.762
You're what?

26:36.597 --> 26:38.056
I'm sorry.

26:38.140 --> 26:41.935
I'm sorry. Yeah, I was just--
I was driving by, and I saw the sign.

26:43.187 --> 26:44.396
It's a great house.

26:44.980 --> 26:46.106
It was.

26:47.274 --> 26:48.734
How do you like the neighborhood?

26:48.817 --> 26:52.863
I don't mean to be rude,
but I'm losing my house.

26:52.946 --> 26:56.033
I'm not selling it. So, you know...

26:56.116 --> 26:58.577
-Get the hell off my lawn?
-Yeah, something like that.

26:59.453 --> 27:01.496
Okay. Well, good luck.

27:01.580 --> 27:02.664
Thank you.

27:19.014 --> 27:20.015
Okay.

27:24.436 --> 27:28.398
I never thought of myself
as the office-affair type.

27:29.775 --> 27:31.527
How long did you and Josh date?

27:31.610 --> 27:35.280
It wasn't really dating.
We enjoyed each other.

27:36.323 --> 27:37.699
An entanglement?

27:41.537 --> 27:44.206
He was in Beijing
when I found out I was pregnant.

27:44.289 --> 27:45.999
Well, did you ever tell him?

27:46.083 --> 27:47.709
By the time he got back from China...

27:49.962 --> 27:52.965
We'd met in Shanghai.

27:54.174 --> 27:57.010
I couldn't bring myself
to tell Josh about the baby,

27:57.761 --> 28:00.097
so I put him up for adoption.

28:00.180 --> 28:01.515
You stay in touch?

28:01.598 --> 28:03.559
Not until Drew found me.

28:04.685 --> 28:09.982
I reached out to explain myself,
but he never returned the call.

28:10.566 --> 28:12.484
Did your boys ever get to meet?

28:12.568 --> 28:14.152
Just on the phone.

28:15.529 --> 28:18.031
I wanted Tim to know he had a big brother.

28:19.658 --> 28:22.661
I took a screenshot
from our last FaceTime.

28:25.664 --> 28:29.126
He has my grandfather's smile,
and I wanted him to see.

28:33.255 --> 28:34.339
May I?

28:34.840 --> 28:36.216
What is it?

28:37.301 --> 28:40.220
It looks like Shelter housing.

28:40.304 --> 28:41.972
It's Ramon's apartment.

28:42.055 --> 28:44.057
He said he was at his boyfriend's place.

28:49.938 --> 28:51.273
Thank you.

29:24.473 --> 29:26.517
Hey, hey, hey. Hold on, hold on.

29:28.894 --> 29:29.895
You good?

29:30.938 --> 29:33.232
My boss thinks
I was fucking her dead husband.

29:34.024 --> 29:35.359
How's that for a good morning?

29:35.984 --> 29:37.152
Were you?

29:38.362 --> 29:39.947
He didn't like dick, trust me.

29:41.323 --> 29:42.324
Memento?

29:44.284 --> 29:45.869
My ex spilled the wine on it.

29:46.995 --> 29:48.830
I'm taking it to the dry cleaner.

29:49.957 --> 29:50.958
Bad breakup, huh?

29:52.835 --> 29:54.002
You could say that.

30:28.161 --> 30:30.163
Ramon and Drew?

30:30.664 --> 30:33.500
Apparently, there was
an ugly breakup a few weeks ago.

30:34.084 --> 30:36.503
Maybe Ramon thought Drew was seeing Josh.

30:38.046 --> 30:41.508
Jealous boyfriend. Boss's husband.

30:42.050 --> 30:43.051
Hell of a motive.

30:43.886 --> 30:45.012
That's an angle.

30:45.637 --> 30:47.306
An investigation into Ramon.

30:47.389 --> 30:52.311
Overlooked assistant turned
jealous boyfriend turned tragic murderer.

30:53.312 --> 30:57.691
Motive, no evidence. We have to be smart.

31:01.612 --> 31:03.197
When we were in the military,

31:03.280 --> 31:04.907
me and Noble were in the same unit.

31:04.990 --> 31:08.243
Our superior officers would force
the Black enlisted men

31:08.327 --> 31:10.162
to fight each other
while they placed bets.

31:10.829 --> 31:15.167
There was this one officer.
Real junkyard dog redneck.

31:15.667 --> 31:20.756
And one day, this motherfucker tried
to get me and Noble

31:20.839 --> 31:22.799
to fight each other to the death.

31:23.926 --> 31:26.136
We took one look at each other,
and we just--

31:27.471 --> 31:30.599
We just whipped his ass.

31:31.099 --> 31:33.393
I mean, we whipped
this motherfucker's ass.

31:33.477 --> 31:38.023
I mean, we just-- We stomped him, just--
